FOR FILLIES AND MARES THREE YEARS OLD AND UPWARD WHICH HAVE STARTED FOR A CLAIMING PRICE OF $5,000 OR LESS IN 2022 - 2023 OR CLAIMING PRICE $10,000. Three Year Olds, 124 lbs.; Older, 126 lbs. Non-winners Of Two Races Since October 3 Allowed 2 lbs. A Race Since Then Allowed 4 lbs. Claiming Price $10,000 (Races Where Entered For $4,000 Or Less Not Considered For Allowances).
RACE.FOOTNOTES: PINO IN A PURSE took command from the onset, pulled away from pair of chasing rivals through the turn, opened up mildly straightening out for home and had something left for the drive to hold safe from the closing runner in deep stretch. WINYAH BAY was allowed to settle trailing down the backside, started picking up horses four wide circling foes at the quarter pole, loomed the main threat outside in the four path finding her best stride at the top of the stretch, was closing in through the lane but could not get there at the wire. DREAMING OF AUDREY stalked near the rear on the outside, made little headway running through the turn and showed good late energy in the final eighth to rally in deep stretch to capture third money. FEDALIA improved on the fence at the half, nestled smartly behind on the rail just behind the winner throughout the turn, was in the mix of things inside turning for home but stalled at the furlong pole to settle on the fringes. SONET'S NAME chased between foes down the back straight, sat just outside and behind the winner around the bend, could not go on with others at the top of the lane and weakened in mid-stretch. AMERICAN GAMBLE tracked the frontrunner three wide outside horses down the backstretch, kept pace with the winner still travelling three wide on the turn, was nudged on for more at the quarter pole, could not keep up with the front two and flattened out in upper stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: BACHELOR PAD was brushed outside on the break, took control soon after the start, opened up easily down the back straight, was unopposed travelling in hand through the turn and coasted home for the impressive front end score. LAPOCHKA was on the rail having on rival beaten down the backside, edged closer on the rail at the three eighths marker, began to rally shifting outside two furlongs from home, swung out five wide for the stretch run and closed in to be a distant second behind the dominant winner. VICTORY MARCH stalked near the rear on the outside, made little improvement three wide through the turn, was floated out to the seven path for the drive and finished up with intent to close in to be a clear third at the finish line. RACE FOR PINKS travelled in the third flight with runners on each side down the backstretch, was roused in midfield making little progress on the turn, was pushed out to the six path at the top of the lane and finished up willingly between horses down the stretch for a minor role in the end. NEOPHYTE chased the pace in the early stages, came under a ride dueling for the place share well behind the long gone winner at the quarter marker, could not find more in the stretch and faded at the sixteenth pole. SOUPER RIVER settled three deep outside foes down the backstretch in the third flight, offered a mild run around horses three wide at the three furlong pole, was in the hunt on the outside for the runners up share in the three path turning for home, needed more late and tired between runners in the last sixteenth. KEEN FLATTER broke inwards on the start, travelled on the rail in the third flight down the backstretch, was scrubbed on inside trying to keep pace with rivals around the turn and faltered on the fence in upper stretch. BLUE MAX checked mildly between horses soon after the start start to trail down the backside, could not get interested through the turn and was never involved driving to the finish line.

CLAIM.OWNER: Russo Frank and Natural Eight Stable

RACE.FOOTNOTES: ENAHM was unhurried trailing the field in the first turn, crept closer to the field under a snug hold on the fence at the half, had no room to run when surrounded by rivals through the far turn, continued to be blocked by a wall of horses at the top of the stretch, finally angled out having a clear path inside the eighth pole and closed in quickly under a vigorous hand ride to get up at the wire. CHASING TROUBLE settled near the back in the early going, co-trailed on the outside three wide at the half, swooped around runners making a bold move five wide at the quarter pole, seized the lead with a sixteenth to run bit could not hold off the surging winner at the finish. THIS DUDE A BREEZE travelled in midfield down the backstretch, made an early move forcing the pace three wide at the three eighths pole around foes, shifted out in the five path fighting for the lead with with multiple runners at the top of the lane, briefly poked his head in front at the furlong pole, could not hold off the top two finishers late and held for the show money at the line. THE NEW MAYBE assumed the lead after the start, had trouble navigating the first turn bearing out, maintained a slim advantage while hounded outside down the back straight, dueled on the fence on the final turn and faded in the last eighth holding on for a small piece of the prize at the wire. DARE TO BE KING tracked in the second flight on the outside down the backstretch, took closer order through the far turn, was in the mix of things in the four path with the field spread across the pole at the top of the stretch, could not find another gear late and was outfinished in the final furlong. STEADY PROGRESS pressed the issue inside in the first turn, was reined back to track the engaging leaders down the backside, nestled patiently on the fence around the far turn and offered little rally in tight quarters on the rail down the stretch. WAR IN CHARGE was pushed out while prompting the pace outside in the first turn, hounded the leader outside down the backstretch, battled stubbornly outside through the far turn and gave way while surrounded by others in mid-stretch.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: CLASSIC DANCER broke alertly, went straight to the front to set the pace in the clear shifting in but racing just off the rail, drifted out in mid-stretch, held. FABLED PRINCE tracked from inside, came off the fence at the top of the stretch then moved back inside the drifting leader in upper stretch, was within striking distance inside coming to the furlong grounds but ran on evenly late. SOCIETY'S THUNDER stalked from outside the second group advancing while moving in from four to three wide on the turn, was carried out a bit leaving that bend by the leader and eventual winner then again nearing mid-stretch, evened out. TRINITY PARK chased three to four wide, kept on. DREAM ON BABY broke a step slowly and veered out, was carried out by the loose horse up the backstretch, took back and angled in racing two wide into the turn then nearer the rail, altered course outside foes in mid-stretch and ran on. WALTER ME LAD was bumped at the start by the riderless horse, tracked from between runners about two wide, dropped back nearing the quarter pole continuing in behind and off the fence, lacked the needed late kick. DIAMOND HEIST moved out at the start to avoid the loose horse and falling rider then was placed in tight quarters by that foe, carried out several paths, took back and shifted back in tracking in behind in the four path into the turn, was encouraged by the quarter pole, moved out further in upper stretch and lacked the needed late kick. MAGNIFICENT MARIO angled in early, saved ground inside well back of the leader, angled out nine wide in upper stretch, was not a threat. AGILE DANCER stumbled at the start, losing the rider and bumping the inside foe, chased without a jockey racing up close to the leader, was caught by the outrider past the wire and walked off. FOLLOWING A STEWARDS' INQUIRY INTO THE START IT WAS DETERMINED EVERY RUNNER RECEIVED A FAIR BEGINNING AND NO ACTION WAS TAKEN.

PALIO stalked in the third flight three deep down the backside, was roused on the turn but was losing positioning to inside rivals and had nothing to offer in stretch drive. RACE.RACE_TEXT: Valedictory S. - Grade3 WOODBINE RACE 7 1 1/2M All Weather Track CR: 106. Stakes Purse 150000. FOR THREE-YEAR-OLDS AND UPWARD.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: CONGLOMERATE was nestled on the rail in the third flight under a good gallop in the beginning, edged closer to the leaders down the backstretch, patiently waited to pounce inside around the final bend, crept closer by the quarter pole, angled out to the four path driving to the wire, was set down outside in upper stretch full of run and drew off sharply in the final sixteenth for the score. COLLECTIVE FORCE was alone in midfield under the wire for the first time, weaved through horses commencing a run at the three furlong marker, saved ground shifting inwards for clear run on the rail in upper stretch, rallied inside down the lane, angled outside off the tiring early pacesetter at the sixteenth pole and just got up for second money under a heads up ride at the wire. WIN FOR THE MONEY assumed command from the onset, slowed the pace down nicely after three quarters were run, comfortably setting an honest pace, put away the chasing rival in upper stretch, braced for the challenge from the winner at the eighth pole, offered little resistance and faded late just being nabbed for the place share before the finish line. PALAZZI was situated near the back three wide outside foes with a half mile to run, started to pass runners extending his stride three wide with seven sixteenths from home, swung out with momentum widest in the eight path at the top of the stretch and closed in strongly full of run late to settle on the fringes in the end. WAR COURT was in a good position going pass the wire for the first time watching the front trio up top, closed the gap on the front group along the backside, was roused at the quarter pole, angled out in the six path straightening out for the drive in the mix of things for a share and mildly finished up to the wire. SO HIGH (GB) was under a good hold tracking the pacesetter on the rail, shifted outside to offer a challenge three wide at the top of the lane, battled in upper stretch, could not find another gear at the furlong marker and faded slightly in the final sixteenth. MILLIE GIRL stalked in the third flight three wide outside horses in the early stages, began to smartly pick up runners at the seven sixteenths pole, inched closer through the far turn, angled out seven wide turning for home and gamely battled to the wire, never giving in running against the boys. JIM'S HOPE travelled in mid-pack saving ground on the rail early on, offered a mild run on the fence going by rivals at the quarter pole and was one paced inside through the stretch. PRIDEOFDISTINCTION stalked near the back of the pack between foes in the beginning, had one rival beaten travelling down the backside, made little gain when urged on the final turn, angled outside in the six path turning for home but could not be a presence in the stretch running. ENGLISH CONQUEROR was situated near the rear three wide outside horses on the first turn, crept closer when roused at the three eighths marker and could not make any impact running down the stretch. MEYER had a good spot outside, content to track the leader in the early stages on the race, was asked for more two wide three furlongs out to go after the frontrunner, offered little response and yielded in the two path between horses in upper stretch. SEVENTYSEVEN STONE trailed the pack on the fence in the early going, passed some rivals saving ground in the second turn, was relegated to the back of the field at the three eighths pole again and resurged to pass some weary runners in the stretch. LUCKMAN was unhurried, seeing the field into the second turn, made little improvement on the rail down the back straight and and had nothing to show in the drive to the finish line. RAPPER ZAPPER was shuffled back some jockeying for position on the first turn between foes, advanced nicely on the outside getting a better spot down the backstretch, was urged midway on the final turn, could not go on with others and retreated inside in upper stretch.
